Activity: A13 - Discover 5 unique online security tools

Objective
The goal of this activity was to identify security tools that operate online to protect systems, networks, and user data from cyber threats.

Method
I explored various online platforms and tools that providesecurity srevices such as malware scanning, vulnerability detection, and secure communication. i observed how these tools function and what type of protection they offer

Findings
The following online security tools were identified:
1. VirusTotal - allows users to upload files or URLs to scan for malware using multiple antivirus engines
2. Cloudfare - provides protection against DDoS attacks and improves website security through filtering and monitoring traffic
3. Have I Been Pwned - checks if an email or password has been exposed in known data breaches
4. Qualys SSL Labs - analyses website SSL/TLS configurations to identify security weaknesses
5. Cisco Umbrella - protects users by blocking access to malicious domains at the DNS level

Security Principle
These tools support confidentiality, integrity, and availability by detecting threats, preventing unauthorised access, and ensuring secure communication over the internet

